178
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:03,000
If you see anyone suspicious, report them!

179
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:09,000
♬〜

180
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:11,000
(Investigator) We have arrived under the building.

181
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:35,000
♬〜

182
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:37,000
It won't come.

183
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:44,000
♬〜

184
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:50,000
🖥️(Announcer) It appears that a kidnapping incident occurred in Tokyo this afternoon.

185
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:53,000
🖥️The person who was kidnapped was the wife of a National Police Agency employee→

186
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:56,000
Nanae Kurimura, 41 years old.

187
00:12:57,000 --> 00:13:02,000
🖥️Victim's safety Details such as contact between the perpetrator and the police are not known.

188
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:07,000
Photos of the best stars are popping up all over social media.

189
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:12,000
♬〜

190
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:15,000
Hey... Lend me your bag.

191
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:17,000
Ah yes.

192
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:19,000
Replace the transmitter battery inside.

193
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:25,000
ring!?

194
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:27,000
I thought I'd propose as a surprise!

195
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:32,000
Listen to what you said earlier→

196
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:37,000
I wanted to forget about the painful things from the past.

197
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:39,000
I see...! Then...!

198
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:41,000
yeah? Ah, this?

199
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:45,000
Well, I'll get it anyway, but I can't put it on my finger yet.

200
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:48,000
Didn't like it?

201
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:51,000
no. I'm teasing you.

202
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:53,000
What is it? that. The worst!

203
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:58,000
Huh?

204
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:04,000
Block!? No, there's no money in it?

205
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:07,000
Sigh….

206
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:11,000
Private key of digital currency.

207
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:15,000
The criminal demanded 100 million yen in crypto assets.

208
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:20,000
Now I'm going to access the exchange and steal the money.

209
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:24,000
No, if I just had to give it to you, I wouldn't have to make it so heavy...

210
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:26,000
It's the atmosphere. It's important, right?

211
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:29,000
No, the atmosphere... Okay, okay.

212
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:31,000
It was really heavy, wasn't it? Yes, yes, put it in.

213
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:35,000
It's already been two hours. Why are there no instructions?

214
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:39,000
Did you run away because you thought you wouldn't get the ransom?

215
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:41,000
Then the hostages are in danger.

216
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:43,000
surely….

217
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:47,000
Chief. Why was there a ransom demand on the manager's phone?

218
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:52,000
Also, the culprit was telling the manager to wake up.

219
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:54,000
What does that mean?

220
00:14:56,000 --> 00:15:00,000
What's going on? The situation is fixed.

221
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:04,000
Ah, that looks delicious. (Swan) Ah... please.

222
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:07,000
Stop it. I'll break my tooth again.

223
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:09,000
It's an emergency right now, so there's no gimmick.

224
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:11,000
please. (Masuda) Then...

225
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:13,000
(Suguro) Hey, who's in charge of special crimes?

226
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:16,000
They're experts at kidnapping cases, right?

227
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:19,000
Yes, they are also pursuing the looters in a parallel investigation.

228
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:24,000
Witness information is gathering when a hostage was taken in a supermarket parking lot.

229
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:28,000
The perpetrators were three men. It seems like it was done well.

230
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:30,000
What about security cameras?

231
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:33,000
I'm doing it. Determine the license plate number of the car carrying the hostages.

232
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:36,000
But why?

233
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:40,000
Why did they kidnap a police officer's wife?

234
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:43,000
After all, it's the place a criminal would want to mess with the most, right?

235
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:47,000
Employees say they have no recollection of it.

236
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:51,000
Her husband is a subordinate of Deputy Chief Cabinet Secretary Akase.

237
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:56,000
(Masuda) The Deputy Chief Cabinet Secretary is the older brother of the section chief.

238
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:02,000
Ah... that's right.

239
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:08,000
Huh... Is the section chief's brother also a police officer?

240
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:11,000
i don't know.

241
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:16,000
Waiting for a call from the criminal.

242
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:20,000
Stay ready to launch at any time! (All) Yes!

243
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:29,000
♬〜

244
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:33,000
A phone call from the criminal? Did something suspicious happen?

245
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:35,000
I don't know yet.

246
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:41,000
♬〜

247
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:44,000
🔊 (Voice changer's voice) Proceed along Niimi Street to Ashitomi Town.

248
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:46,000
🔊Until 5:15pm.

249
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:48,000
🔊(noise)

250
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:52,000
(Train running sound)

251
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:57,000
♬〜

252
00:16:57,000 --> 00:16:59,000
(Swan) Uh...!

253
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:01,000
Oh my...! Ugh...!

254
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:04,000
Ugh...! Ugh...!

255
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:08,000
Mio-nee isn't here...

256
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:11,000
Beautiful sister? here we go….

257
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:19,000
♬〜

258
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:23,000
(sound of tapping)

259
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:27,000
(sound of tapping)

