00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:31,000
(sound of tapping)

261
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:35,000
(Souichiro Midorikawa) Oh... Bisei-nee! what up?

262
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:41,000
If you were listening to the voices of the plunderers→

263
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:45,000
Behind me, I heard the sound of an air sander removing paint.

264
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:52,000
This is a machine that produces a sound exceeding 2000 hertz and is only found in repair shops.

265
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:57,000
That sound.

266
00:17:57,000 --> 00:17:59,000
(operating sound)

267
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:02,000
(Mio) Others→

268
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:05,000
I could also hear the sound of tires hitting the wheels.

269
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:09,000
That sound.

270
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:11,000
What is that?

271
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:16,000
You can also hear the sound of trains in the distance from here.

272
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:20,000
(Mio) Mecha old man...

273
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:23,000
Did you suddenly say you were quitting?

274
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:26,000
I decided to retire today.

275
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:28,000
Old wounds hurt.

276
00:18:28,000 --> 00:18:31,000
I asked for the first star.

277
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:36,000
♬〜

278
00:18:36,000 --> 00:18:40,000
(Miqing) I heard noise from the words.

279
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:43,000
That's what I learned from you.

280
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:50,000
(Mio) ``Car engines make strange noises when they're not running well.''

281
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:56,000
``Don't ignore that. It's the same with people.''

282
00:18:56,000 --> 00:19:01,000
``When people lie, they make noise.''

283
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:05,000
What do you want to say?

284
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:10,000
Why did the culprit call me from here?

285
00:19:16,066 --> 00:19:19,066
Why did the culprit call me from here?

286
00:19:23,066 --> 00:19:27,066
Is the culprit here? Hostages too?

287
00:19:28,066 --> 00:19:30,066
Did you come alone?

288
00:19:31,066 --> 00:19:33,066
What is that?

289
00:19:34,066 --> 00:19:38,066
You were taught to always have a buddy when investigating.

290
00:19:39,066 --> 00:19:41,066
It's dangerous if there are two or more culprits.

291
00:19:42,066 --> 00:19:44,066
Is there one?

292
00:19:47,066 --> 00:19:51,066
(Mobile phone ringtone)

293
00:19:52,066 --> 00:19:54,066
It's Akase!

294
00:19:55,066 --> 00:19:57,066
Give instructions.

295
00:19:57,066 --> 00:20:00,066
Go to the Kasumigaseki National Police Agency Building.

296
00:20:00,066 --> 00:20:02,066
National Police Agency!?

297
00:20:06,066 --> 00:20:08,066
Why is this happening...

298
00:20:08,066 --> 00:20:16,066
♬〜

299
00:20:16,066 --> 00:20:18,066
(Midorikawa) Would you like me to leave?

300
00:20:21,066 --> 00:20:23,066
Try to catch me.

301
00:20:23,066 --> 00:20:36,066
♬〜

302
00:20:36,066 --> 00:20:40,066
For me…→

303
00:20:40,066 --> 00:20:43,066
I don't have the right to arrest you.

304
00:20:50,066 --> 00:20:53,066
(Isozaki) Understood.

305
00:20:53,066 --> 00:20:57,066
The Mobile Investigation Headquarters vehicle is moved to the National Police Agency as per the criminal's instructions.

306
00:20:57,066 --> 00:21:00,066
Don't make me come here. Stop it.

307
00:21:04,066 --> 00:21:09,066
(Mio) I am a traitor.

308
00:21:10,066 --> 00:21:13,066
I was monitoring Chief Akase.

309
00:21:14,066 --> 00:21:19,066
Regarding Manager Akase, there has been no suspicious behavior so far...

310
00:21:23,066 --> 00:21:25,066
This is Amao.

311
00:21:25,066 --> 00:21:28,066
Chief Akase is starting to do something other than giving orders.

312
00:21:30,066 --> 00:21:32,066
Continue to keep an eye on your brother.

313
00:21:33,066 --> 00:21:35,066
(Mio) The manager's brother told me...

314
00:21:39,066 --> 00:21:41,066
(Mobile phone ringtone)

315
00:21:41,066 --> 00:21:45,066
📞(Voice changer voice) What are you doing? Head to the National Police Agency quickly!

316
00:21:45,066 --> 00:21:48,066
I contacted my superiors, but they told me not to move.

317
00:21:48,066 --> 00:21:51,066
What should happen to the hostages?

318
00:21:51,066 --> 00:21:59,066
♬〜

319
00:21:59,066 --> 00:22:01,066
Got it.

320
00:22:01,066 --> 00:22:04,066
(Man) When you get to the National Police Agency, gather the media.

321
00:22:08,066 --> 00:22:10,066
The media...?

322
00:22:10,066 --> 00:22:16,066
♬〜

323
00:22:16,066 --> 00:22:20,066
I was in a hurry. Every day passes quickly...

324
00:22:22,066 --> 00:22:25,066
(Mio) Became a police officer as a non-career →

325
00:22:25,066 --> 00:22:32,066
I studied criminal psychology and helped solve cases.

326
00:22:32,066 --> 00:22:35,066
I have received the Chief's Award many times...

327
00:22:38,066 --> 00:22:46,066
I was embarrassed, but inside I was excited because I was getting closer to my dream.

328
00:22:48,066 --> 00:22:52,066
I don't have any friends, I don't want to get married.

329
00:22:52,066 --> 00:22:56,066
Because he was called to the Head Office's First Investigative Division.

330
00:23:01,066 --> 00:23:09,066
But every day passes by chasing after small incidents...

331
00:23:12,066 --> 00:23:19,066
I see... I realized that I was going to be stopped by the local police station after all...

332
00:23:23,066 --> 00:23:25,066
(Mio) Once before →

333
00:23:25,066 --> 00:23:33,066
I proposed to the National Police Agency that the conditions at detention facilities should be improved.

334
00:23:33,066 --> 00:23:38,066
Did you see that from Deputy Chief Cabinet Secretary Akase?

335
00:23:39,066 --> 00:23:41,066
(Mio) Mobile Investigation Division?

336
00:23:46,066 --> 00:23:49,066
Would you like to work there too?

337
00:23:50,066 --> 00:23:55,066
This is an investigation team that I created that reports directly to the National Police Agency.

338
00:23:55,066 --> 00:23:57,066
National Police Agency….

339
00:23:59,066 --> 00:24:01,066
Commit to a career path.

340
00:24:03,066 --> 00:24:07,066
I obtained the national civil service qualification and joined the National Police Agency mid-career.

341
00:24:10,066 --> 00:24:12,066
Yes, willingly.

342
00:24:15,066 --> 00:24:20,066
The head of the Mobile Investigation Division is my younger brother.

343
00:24:20,066 --> 00:24:22,066
Is that so?

344
00:24:22,066 --> 00:24:26,066
My younger brother acts strangely when he's not doing his job.

345
00:24:30,066 --> 00:24:34,066
Please keep an eye on my brother and report to me.

346
00:24:35,066 --> 00:24:37,066
(Mio's voice) I was told to become a spy...

347
00:24:39,066 --> 00:24:43,066
I was so scared that my hands were shaking.

348
00:24:43,066 --> 00:24:47,066
But they said they would put me in the career group...

349
00:24:49,066 --> 00:24:55,066
Then you're going to get me for that bastard?

350
00:24:58,066 --> 00:25:00,066
No.

351
00:25:04,066 --> 00:25:06,066
I'm heading to Kasumigaseki.

352
00:25:06,066 --> 00:25:14,066
(Police car siren)

353
00:25:14,066 --> 00:25:16,066
Oh!?

354
00:25:16,066 --> 00:25:36,066
♬〜

355
00:25:36,066 --> 00:25:39,066
Manager I can't move.

356
00:25:39,066 --> 00:25:41,066
Mr. Kuro.

357
00:25:41,066 --> 00:25:53,066
♬〜

358
00:25:55,066 --> 00:25:58,066
I made a friend.

359
00:26:01,066 --> 00:26:07,066
Everyone recognized me...

360
00:26:07,066 --> 00:26:15,066
♬〜

361
00:26:15,066 --> 00:26:18,066
(Mio's voice) Every day was fulfilling.

362
00:26:20,066 --> 00:26:23,066
To betray my friends...

363
00:26:26,066 --> 00:26:28,066
My heart feels like it's going to burst...

364
00:26:34,066 --> 00:26:40,066
Also, I have doubts about that Deputy Chief Cabinet Secretary.

365
00:26:40,066 --> 00:26:44,066
What is the relationship between that person and Manager Akase?

366
00:26:44,066 --> 00:26:48,066
Why does the older brother hate his younger brother?

367
00:26:49,066 --> 00:26:52,066
I can't answer it in one word.

368
00:26:53,066 --> 00:26:56,066
Does it have something to do with kidnapping?

369
00:26:56,066 --> 00:27:01,066
ah. Kidnapping isn't about money.

370
00:27:04,066 --> 00:27:09,066
It is true that the kidnappers used this as their stronghold.

371
00:27:13,066 --> 00:27:19,066
Up until now, I've tinkered with mechanics and repaired them, but I've also broken them.

372
00:27:23,066 --> 00:27:26,066
I have no hesitation in destroying people.

373
00:27:30,066 --> 00:27:33,066
It's not that I hate you.

374
00:27:33,066 --> 00:27:39,066
♬〜

375
00:27:39,066 --> 00:27:41,066
He said he had made a friend.

376
00:27:48,066 --> 00:27:52,066
We also have no hesitation in shooting people.

377
00:27:52,066 --> 00:27:55,066
Mio-nee: It's a long story.

378
00:27:55,066 --> 00:28:03,066
♬〜

379
00:28:03,066 --> 00:28:07,066
I don't think he committed this incident for money.

380
00:28:07,066 --> 00:28:11,066
But I'll arrest you.

381
00:28:11,066 --> 00:28:13,066
Because we're friends.

382
00:28:16,066 --> 00:28:21,066
Charge of conspiracy to commit kidnapping for ransom.

383
00:28:21,066 --> 00:28:25,066
Executed at 9:15.

384
00:28:28,066 --> 00:28:30,066
ᗒ (noise)

385
00:28:30,066 --> 00:28:32,066
I'm going over there.

386
00:28:36,066 --> 00:28:39,066
Wait! Wait!

387
00:28:39,066 --> 00:28:48,066
♬〜

388
00:28:48,066 --> 00:28:50,066
Mr. Kurimura! (Nanae) Ugh... Ugh...!

389
00:28:51,066 --> 00:28:53,066
OK?

390
00:28:53,066 --> 00:28:57,066
(Basic) Protect hostages. He is safe and unharmed.

391
00:28:57,066 --> 00:29:01,066
Thank you for your hard work. The perpetrator is on the run. Emergency deployment please.

392
00:29:01,066 --> 00:29:03,066
(Investigator) Yes.

393
00:29:03,066 --> 00:29:13,066
♬〜

394
00:29:13,066 --> 00:29:15,066
Mecha old man!?

395
00:29:15,066 --> 00:29:18,066
Huh... what do you mean?

396
00:29:26,066 --> 00:29:28,066
Mecha old man!?

397
00:29:28,066 --> 00:29:31,066
Huh... what do you mean?

398
00:29:32,066 --> 00:29:35,066
He was involved in a kidnapping case.

399
00:29:35,066 --> 00:29:39,066
Huh!? I don't understand it anymore!

400
00:29:39,066 --> 00:29:42,066
So I knew a lot about trucks.

401
00:29:45,066 --> 00:29:50,066
I thought the chef could meet the demands and drive safely.

402
00:29:50,066 --> 00:29:56,066
It was to appeal to the media and I didn't want an accident.

403
00:30:00,066 --> 00:30:02,066
(Shingo) Identify the culprit. Faster than my brother.

404
00:30:02,066 --> 00:30:05,066
Understood. Ah... that...

405
00:30:06,066 --> 00:30:08,066
Can I go see my wife?

406
00:30:09,066 --> 00:30:11,066
Do your job.

407
00:30:11,066 --> 00:30:37,066
♬〜

408
00:30:37,066 --> 00:30:41,066
It's difficult to do, but we'll interrogate you using normal procedures.

409
00:30:43,066 --> 00:30:45,066
What's your name?

410
00:30:45,066 --> 00:30:47,066
remain silent.

411
00:30:47,066 --> 00:30:49,066
Mecha old man...!

412
00:30:50,066 --> 00:30:52,066
I wanted to say it once.

413
00:30:52,066 --> 00:30:54,066
Don't kid yourself.

414
00:30:56,066 --> 00:30:59,066
It's tension and relaxation.

415
00:31:01,066 --> 00:31:04,066
Please tell me the name of your fellow plunderer.

416
00:31:04,066 --> 00:31:08,066
They're not comrades... they're comrades.

417
00:31:10,066 --> 00:31:14,066
Ugh... Hmph Hmph Hmph!

418
00:31:14,066 --> 00:31:16,066
Okay!

419
00:31:16,066 --> 00:31:25,066
♬〜

420
00:31:25,066 --> 00:31:29,066
This is Jissoji, Life Safety Planning Division, Life Safety Bureau, National Police Agency.

421
00:31:31,066 --> 00:31:34,066
Kinjo, Traffic Regulation Division, Traffic Bureau, National Police Agency.

422
00:31:36,066 --> 00:31:40,066
My name is Tatebayashi, Audit Office, Accounting Division, Commissioner's Secretariat, National Police Agency.

423
00:31:42,066 --> 00:31:45,066
Nice to meet you, Midorikawa-senpai.

424
00:31:48,066 --> 00:31:51,066
(Midorikawa) What about Shingo Akase?

425
00:31:51,066 --> 00:31:54,066
(Jitssoji) Yes. I would like to ask you about that.

426
00:31:54,066 --> 00:31:59,066
At the age of 55, he became Deputy Chief Cabinet Secretary in the Criminal Division.

427
00:31:59,066 --> 00:32:01,066
He will become the chief of security this year.

428
00:32:01,066 --> 00:32:06,066
If that happens, he will become one of the top eight members of the National Police Agency.

429
00:32:06,066 --> 00:32:09,066
After that, the Deputy Director-General's default route...

430
00:32:09,066 --> 00:32:12,066
Because I did the dirty work...

431
00:32:12,066 --> 00:32:16,066
do you guys know? About the cleaner.

432
00:32:18,066 --> 00:32:20,066
Midorikawa-senpai too...

433
00:32:20,066 --> 00:32:25,066
ah. He's called a cleaner behind his back.

434
00:32:28,066 --> 00:32:31,066
(Tatebayashi's voice) Scandals that occurred within the police and the ruling party→

435
00:32:31,066 --> 00:32:35,066
A cleaner who disposes of things in the dark without showing them to the public.

436
00:32:36,066 --> 00:32:38,066
Stop me before I show up.

437
00:32:38,066 --> 00:32:42,066
Understood. We will handle it here.

438
00:32:43,066 --> 00:32:48,066
(Kinjo's voice) Protecting executives who caused scandals by using the public security department and riot police→

439
00:32:48,066 --> 00:32:53,066
They have disposed of those involved and buried those who sniffed around.

440
00:32:55,066 --> 00:32:58,066
I don't like it, I don't like it...please stop it! Wow!

441
00:32:58,066 --> 00:33:01,066
(Jitssoji Temple) Akase Shingo's achievements →

442
00:33:01,066 --> 00:33:04,066
He is trying to rise to the top of the National Police Agency.

443
00:33:04,066 --> 00:33:06,066
Have you looked into it?

444
00:33:06,066 --> 00:33:09,066
It's been a few years since I heard the rumors.

445
00:33:10,066 --> 00:33:14,066
Do you understand? What happens when you sniff around?

446
00:33:16,066 --> 00:33:19,066
You're doing something dangerous.

447
00:33:23,066 --> 00:33:28,066
Mecha-ji was the first to find out about his brother's wrongdoing.

448
00:33:29,066 --> 00:33:34,066
20 years ago, when it was still part of the First Investigative Division.

449
00:33:37,066 --> 00:33:42,066
My brother, a young bureaucrat, covered up the murder of a police officer.

450
00:33:43,066 --> 00:33:48,066
When the mecha old man found out about it, he couldn't forgive him →

451
00:33:48,066 --> 00:33:52,066
Even if it was a relative, he would defend himself against arrest.

452
00:33:52,066 --> 00:33:54,066
(gunshot)

453
00:33:54,066 --> 00:33:56,066
(Woman's scream)

454
00:33:56,066 --> 00:34:00,066
(Akase's voice) I was so injured that I couldn't return to the field, so I went to the equipment department...

455
00:34:00,066 --> 00:34:03,066
(Sigh) So it's been cleaned.

456
00:34:10,066 --> 00:34:14,066
This guy is just like me and is honestly an idiot.

457
00:34:21,066 --> 00:34:26,066
Before I came here, I was in the second division.

458
00:34:28,066 --> 00:34:32,066
Focusing on bribery by ruling party politicians →

459
00:34:32,066 --> 00:34:37,066
While following the flow of money, he found his brother.

460
00:34:37,066 --> 00:34:44,066
Some of the ruling party's policy funds were transferred to my brother's personal account.

461
00:34:44,066 --> 00:34:48,066
As a personal activity expense that can be used freely.

462
00:34:50,066 --> 00:34:54,066
Hey, aren't you an idiot?

463
00:34:54,066 --> 00:34:58,066
Don't look away from this guy either...

464
00:34:58,066 --> 00:35:04,066
♬〜

465
00:35:04,066 --> 00:35:06,066
Brother.

466
00:35:09,066 --> 00:35:11,066
There is something I would like to ask you.

467
00:35:14,066 --> 00:35:18,066
My brother used his personnel authority to remove me from the second section.

468
00:35:18,066 --> 00:35:20,066
Give me a supervisor.

469
00:35:23,066 --> 00:35:28,066
Don't blame Miao-nee. I'm reflecting on it.

470
00:35:30,066 --> 00:35:32,066
I don't think so.

471
00:35:34,066 --> 00:35:39,066
Thanks to everyone's hard work, the department's arrest rate was high.

472
00:35:39,066 --> 00:35:44,066
But that's not the purpose of this lesson.

473
00:35:46,066 --> 00:35:53,066
I was also cleaned.

474
00:35:53,066 --> 00:35:56,066
So the culprit says, ``Wake up!''

475
00:35:59,066 --> 00:36:07,066
Actually, I'm trapped here.

476
00:36:10,066 --> 00:36:15,066
The first star is a prison.

477
00:36:17,066 --> 00:36:24,066
It's dark and cold and I can't escape →

478
00:36:24,066 --> 00:36:26,066
It's a prison.

479
00:36:26,066 --> 00:36:36,066
♬〜

480
00:36:37,066 --> 00:36:40,066
(camera shutter sound)

481
00:36:42,066 --> 00:36:44,066
(Nemoto) The criminal's fingerprints were found.

482
00:36:44,066 --> 00:36:49,066
The hostage remembered the criminal's appearance and the number plate matched by sightings.

483
00:36:49,066 --> 00:36:53,066
The kidnappers are National Police Agency bureaucrats →

484
00:36:53,066 --> 00:37:00,066
Koichi Jissoji, Takuya Kinjo, Keiji Tatebayashi and 3 others!

485
00:37:02,066 --> 00:37:04,066
Excuse me.

486
00:37:06,066 --> 00:37:08,066
We have identified the culprit.

487
00:37:15,066 --> 00:37:17,066
Clean.

488
00:37:18,066 --> 00:37:22,066
Um... I don't understand why →

489
00:37:22,066 --> 00:37:25,066
Why would a National Police Agency official kidnap someone for ransom?

490
00:37:25,066 --> 00:37:30,066
Money is not the goal. I said comrade.

491
00:37:31,066 --> 00:37:36,066
I can't overlook what Shingo Akase is doing. I will inform the world.

492
00:37:37,066 --> 00:37:40,066
Kidnap a subordinate's family and make a fuss in the media →

493
00:37:40,066 --> 00:37:44,066
I will hold an interview with the hostages in front of the National Police Agency.

494
00:37:44,066 --> 00:37:48,066
There is a cleaner within the National Police Agency who has covered up many scandals.

495
00:37:54,066 --> 00:37:57,066
Are you really going to do it?

496
00:37:57,066 --> 00:38:00,066
Even in this era, there were radical reformers.

497
00:38:02,066 --> 00:38:06,066
We are looking for a place to hold hostages.

498
00:38:06,066 --> 00:38:09,066
Please lend me this place.

499
00:38:15,066 --> 00:38:17,066
So you're complicit in the kidnapping?

500
00:38:19,066 --> 00:38:21,066
I will take the punishment.

501
00:38:24,066 --> 00:38:28,066
Before I get sent to the prosecutor's office, please return the money I lent you.

502
00:38:28,066 --> 00:38:30,066
Huh? Have you already given it back?

503
00:38:30,066 --> 00:38:34,066
What are you talking about? I lent it to you every time a new machine came out!

504
00:38:35,066 --> 00:38:37,066
Momoko: That's later...

505
00:38:38,066 --> 00:38:45,066
(Swan) I understand the criminal's feelings, but I still cannot forgive the crime.

506
00:38:45,066 --> 00:38:50,066
No, but there was something we could have done before arresting the culprit.

507
00:38:50,066 --> 00:38:52,066
After all, it's a problem with our organization, right?

508
00:38:52,066 --> 00:38:54,066
A crime is a crime! I don't have time right now.

509
00:38:54,066 --> 00:38:57,066
Where are the three mecha old men?

510
00:38:58,066 --> 00:39:04,066
He said that if there was any trouble with the plan, he would arrest the Deputy Chief Cabinet Secretary.

511
00:39:04,066 --> 00:39:16,066
♬〜

512
00:39:16,066 --> 00:39:18,066
(gunshot)

513
00:39:20,066 --> 00:39:24,066
(People scream)

514
00:39:24,066 --> 00:39:45,066
♬〜

515
00:39:45,066 --> 00:39:47,066
(gunshot)

516
00:39:51,066 --> 00:39:57,066
(People scream)

517
00:39:57,066 --> 00:40:06,066
♬〜

518
00:40:06,066 --> 00:40:08,066
Got it.

519
00:40:10,066 --> 00:40:12,066
Kinjo and Tatebayashi.

520
00:40:13,066 --> 00:40:16,066
Kill one more person quickly.

521
00:40:16,066 --> 00:40:25,066
♬〜

522
00:40:25,066 --> 00:40:27,066
(Mobile phone ringtone)

523
00:40:27,066 --> 00:40:31,066
Please take it. (Mobile phone ringtone)

524
00:40:37,066 --> 00:40:41,066
This is Jissoji Temple. Tatebayashi was shot near the National Police Agency.

525
00:40:41,066 --> 00:40:43,066
Kinjo doesn't answer the phone either.

526
00:40:43,066 --> 00:40:45,066
I'm on the first star. Run away!

527
00:40:45,066 --> 00:40:48,066
This is the parking lot of Chiyoda-ku Central Park.

528
00:40:49,066 --> 00:40:51,066
I'll head over right away.

529
00:40:52,066 --> 00:40:54,066
(Sound of tapping on desk) I've been shot at.

530
00:40:54,066 --> 00:40:57,066
By order of the Deputy Chief Cabinet Secretary?

531
00:40:57,066 --> 00:40:59,066
It's the same as when I was a mecha old man.

532
00:40:59,066 --> 00:41:02,066
You said you were shot at... here in Japan!?

533
00:41:03,066 --> 00:41:06,066
Even if you run away, I'll be unarmed!

534
00:41:13,066 --> 00:41:15,066
There are riot police around!

535
00:41:21,066 --> 00:41:25,066
Chief, please protect me.

536
00:41:27,066 --> 00:41:45,066
♬〜

537
00:41:45,066 --> 00:41:48,066
(Buds voice) There's no point in looking back.

538
00:41:48,066 --> 00:41:50,066
Nothing progresses.

539
00:41:50,066 --> 00:41:53,066
I have to look ahead and live.

540
00:41:53,066 --> 00:41:55,066
I'm still alive!

541
00:41:55,066 --> 00:42:03,066
♬〜

542
00:42:03,066 --> 00:42:05,066
Wait, maybe it's my brother's orders!

543
00:42:05,066 --> 00:42:12,066
♬〜

544
00:42:12,066 --> 00:42:14,066
There is someone I want to protect!

545
00:42:14,066 --> 00:42:18,066
Momoko-san, those guys aren't on our side! Huh? You're a police officer!

546
00:42:18,066 --> 00:42:40,066
♬〜

547
00:42:40,066 --> 00:42:44,066
♬〜

548
00:42:44,066 --> 00:42:47,066
(Isshi Minatomoto) Don't move, don't do anything. Huh!?

549
00:42:52,066 --> 00:42:54,066
Finish it quickly.

550
00:42:54,066 --> 00:42:58,066
♬〜

551
00:42:58,066 --> 00:43:15,066
♬〜

552
00:43:15,066 --> 00:43:17,066
(gunshot)

553
00:43:28,066 --> 00:43:30,066
Are you okay!? Are you okay!?

554
00:43:34,066 --> 00:43:36,066
(gunshot)

555
00:43:41,066 --> 00:43:48,066
♬〜

556
00:43:48,066 --> 00:43:50,066
Momoko-san?

557
00:43:50,066 --> 00:43:52,066
Momoko-san!?

558
00:43:53,066 --> 00:43:55,066
Momoko-san!

559
00:43:55,066 --> 00:43:59,066
The rest...I asked for it...

560
00:44:01,066 --> 00:44:04,066
Momoko-san!

561
00:44:04,066 --> 00:44:06,066
Momoko-san!

562
00:44:06,066 --> 00:44:10,066
(Minatomoto) Mobile Investigation Division, surrender immediately!

563
00:44:12,066 --> 00:44:15,066
Momoko-san!

564
00:44:16,066 --> 00:44:20,066
peach! peach!

565
00:44:23,066 --> 00:44:25,066
Momoko!!
